article.headline: N. Arizona 76, Idaho St. 53
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Kyle Landry scored 14 points and Zarko Comagic added 12 as Northern Arizona beat Idaho State 76-53 Saturday night in the regular-season finale for both teams. Nate Geiser finished with 11 points and Zach Filzen 10 for the Lumberjacks (20-10, 11-5 Big Sky) who have already earned a first-round bye as the No. 2 seed in the upcoming conference tournament. Amorrow Morgan had 12 points for Idaho State (11-18, 8-8) and Matt Stucki scored 10. Northern Arizona scored four points in the final 1:24, capped by a Matt Johnson reverse layup, and took a 36-28 halftime lead. The Lumberjacks then made 54 percent of their field goals in the second half (13-of-24) while Idaho State missed 16 of its 26 shots.
